<issue
  id="nks-71"
  type="arm"
  linkend="Activity_as_realized.Activity_happening"
  category="minor_technical"
  by="Nigel Shaw"
  date="2002-10-23"
  status="closed">
  <description>
The where rule reads:
NotActual: NOT ('Activity_actual' in TYPEOF(predicted));

In fact TYPEOF returns UPPERCASE complete names (i.e. with the schema prepended). Hence this 
has to read:
WR1: NOT ('ACTIVITY_AS_REALIZED.ACTIVITY_ACTUAL' in TYPEOF(predicted));

It is also the STEP convention to use WR1 (for where rule 1) rather than meaningful names 
for rule labels.


   </description>

<comment
   by="Sean Barker" 
   date="2002-12-9">
<description>
Done
</description>
</comment>
 </issue>

